Hills of Norvos072504wloei9il0nje9kaoptvjr6bip1w9671784752015-03-22T03:02:01ZThe Dragon Demands5014364[[Image:Hills of Norvos.png|thumb|right|200px|A map showing the location of the Hills of Norvos on the continent of Essos.]]
The '''Hills of Norvos''' are an extensive range of tall hills and mountains located at the north-western end of the continent of [[Essos]]. They extend from the mainland just south of [[Braavos]] along the north coast as far east as the headland known as [[the Axe]]. The extend south almost as far as [[Dagger Lake]].

The hills are named for the [[Free City]] of [[Norvos]], which is the largest city in the area. The headwaters of most of the major tributaries of the [[Rhoyne]] form in these hills.&lt;ref&gt;[http://viewers-guide.hbo.com/game-of-thrones/season2/#!/locations/pentos/ HBO viewers guide, season 2 map, Pentos entry]&lt;/ref&gt;
